caption: Great salads with endless options for creating your very own!  Fresh choices, portions are just right and although it's slightly pricey, worth the fresh and healthy meal!

My review is based on customer service, the guy who attended me yesterday had a horrendous attitude. I was surprised as I have been here plenty of times and never experienced anything like this before. I won’t be coming back there are other places in Bushwick with friendlier and professional staff members than the ones at this place.
The other day i ordered a chef salad and it was so good.

Food was good, but the guy who took my order was really unfriendly and seemed over it. Saying “it’s right there” when someone asks what dressings are available is rude. Better Bushwick spots with friendly service available.

Great salads and a really great team who have kept going all the way through the pandemic.  So many options for food in Bushwick but sometimes you just need something healthy and this is your place for it.  I love the buffalo chicken salad and their supporting soups are wonderful.  Great work team!
The foods are awesome. they season everything which is a good thing. they're are so many choices to choose from.
Great food and service

Their salads are always fresh and tasty! I've been a fan of this place for a while. The people who work there are friendly and accommodating, too. Today I realized there was a ingredient missing from my salad and called them to let them know - they sent me a corrected order almost immediately at no extra charge.
Good service, fresh veggies but very expensive  and not a lot of meat. I will stick to my deli salads.
Best
The salad was so scrumptious!!! The delivery service was super quick and my favorite thing, THEY ADDED A HAND SANITIZER GEL PACKAGE 🥰😍 Such wonderul gesture in times of covid ❤
Their chicken is so unseasoned. It’s like they place it on bred crumbs without seasoning it then frying it. disgusting.
Loveeee this place, everything is fresh 💚
Love the Asian salad. One of my favorites. Everything taste good. Mandarin dressing is so good. Thanks guys

I had just left this place due to a person working there taking my order then a woman walks in who placed an order either by phone or app. He suddenly stops taking my order to help her which I don’t really understand why because this person could have waited till my order was complete. That was very rude. I was a regular there but I’ll never come back being treated like that.

The ingredients are fresh and there are many toppings to choose from, which is excellent. However, the big issue with this place is consistency in salad sizes. Depending on the employee behind the counter, your salad might be packed all the way to the top or it could be 3/4 full. When paying for a $13 large salad, the container should be completely full and you shouldn't have to walk in hoping to get the right employees that will give you a full meal. If I'm at all hungry for lunch, I often won't go here because I'm not sure if I'll end up satiated.

Just passed by to get my pick up order and was excited about eating it just by looking at it from the bag. My girlfriend and I have no complaints about this place the salads were wet not drenched in dressing. Ingredients tasted fresh not old or soggy. Greatest salad place in the 5 boroughs!

The salads are terrible. It's all dressing and lettuce. I couldn't taste any of the other ingredients. Nothing special. And the staff were unfriendly and uncourteous.

Honestly, I love the paninis. The soups are awesome! The food is great. BUT, one day my boyfriend went in without me and started ordering his meal. When he said espinaca instead of spinach. And the girl who was taking his order starts yelling saying “NO, NO, NO I don’t speak Spanish only English here!” My boyfriend stood there without words because this has never happened to him before. I’m sorry to say that the girl serving him was black. I’m not racist nor am I disrespectful but maybe whoever is in charge of this place should take this review in consideration and do something about it.

The salads here are pretty good, nothing spectacular. Their dressings are what make this place different, and they dont have anything particularly amazing.  The staff is pretty friendly. Especially considering how cramped their workspace is.  The cookies aren't as advertised. I received a peanut butter cookie that either had an accident or was intentionally doused in sea salt. A REAL turn off when you want a sweet snack.  Overall, not the most impressive place. Manhattan prices for ordinary experiences. Go for the friendly staff.
Salad is okay. Nothing special about it and the price you pay for an okay salad – premium. I wouldn’t consider coming back unless prices were lowered substantially.

I agree with the review someone else posted in here. The ingredients aren’t very fresh. The chicken in mine wasn’t grilled and similar to the stuff they serve at subway. I ordered a Cesar with some extras and it came to $14. My Cesar had no croutons, no cheese, and a very small side of dressing. I can get the same salad with fresher Ingredients for the same price at Chopt. Not worth the $$$

Ordered the steak salad. The lettuce had a sour, wet taste to it, as if it had been sitting in fetid water all week. The “steak” was ash-colored and dry. Well, at least the one thumb-tack sized piece of steak I found was.

Not friendly, slow and the Salads are way too expensive.  The large salad was about 6.50, by the time I added everything I wanted it was $10.00 which is fine but then plus tax over $13.00 for a salad and they didn’t even have Shrimp.

I love you guys, come in almost everyday for lunch but there has been a hair in my salad two times in a row. Seriously I’m not a germaphobe and I forgive imperfection but twice in a row on separate days insinuates it’s a consistent problem.

Have enjoyed coming here for a couple years. Great concept, however the salad size and more importantly ingredient quality has been steadily going down while the price remains high.  Many of the ingredients now remind me of the vegetable toppings at Subway.  Hopefully GreenStreet can go back to their old ways!

There are 2 size default healthy salad option in base. And you can make it as unhealthy as you want with add-ons :) I got a large one with flanks steak and parmesan add on and paid 10,90 usd. Small bowl should be OK for a human.  Soups do look good also. Good place for diabetes, vegans and vegeterians.

To start with - I have ordered lunch and dinner both as take out and at the restaurant.  The salads, paninis, and soups are always fresh and consistent. A large salad easily feeds two people.  The flooring in the restaurant is a disaster - the tables and chairs all wobble from how uneven it is, and I've had a shoe get stuck in the flooring on more than one occasion.  If you're looking for a fast, solid lunch spot - this is the place to be.

Terrible service. 2 hours waited for my order. Called 3 times they then realized they wrote my cell phone number wrong. Manager hung up phone on me twice. AVOID  AVOID  AVOID AT ALL COSTS.

They have great panini's and salads here. However, the food has been slowly declining in quality. It used to be awesome, now is just okay. Lastly, getting food delivered from here can take over an hour at times.

Amazing salad spot with a super cool staff! The salads can be a tiny bit pricy. I definitely recommend picking up and eating there as opposed to ordering in as that can be a bit pricey and sometimes the staff at GreenStreets will throw in a few extras here and there :) I miss coming here at least twice a week. Not to mention the soups are stellar and the panini's are out of the world! Wireless internet as well so bring your laptop and chow down!

Didn't try the salads, but the panini were great. We had the chicken parm and chicken caprice. Appropriate portions and the staff was cheerful and helpful. If I have one complaint it's that the menu lists "paninis"... panini is already plural, panino is singular. The sandwiches were tasty either way!

Distinctive salads, huge portions, reasonable prices. The casual, low-key atmosphere makes this a great place to have lunch with friends. Try the soup! I'm sure there's a good reason why they don't serve bread (some of the salads feature tortilla chips) but I can't figure out what that might be.

This place is great. I'm crazy about places being clean. This place is. I need to see that A or I'm out.  The food is very fresh with many options. It's reasonable priced $9 with a drink on average. Depends on your selections. This will fill you up.  I always get it to go. The people who work there can't be any nicer. If something is not to your liking tell them, it's never to late to improve. Good business owners always embrace compliments as well as complaints. If anything changes I will update this post. Chris.
